# ADR-0008: Data access — Repository pattern for portability

> **THE migration-enabler ADR.** Must be in place BEFORE feature #2 ships.

## Context

We accept (adr-0011-fastapi-postgres-b2-backend) that we migrate off managed Supabase to our **FastAPI + Postgres** API (see baller-app-hosting-runbook). If feature code calls `supabase.from('games').select(...)` directly inside widgets/notifiers, that migration is a multi-week rewrite touching every feature.

The cost of building this abstraction now: a few extra files per feature. The cost of NOT building it: weeks of refactor under pressure.

## Decision

**Every data access in the app flows: Widget → Provider/Notifier → Repository (abstract interface) → Concrete Implementation (Supabase today / PocketBase or self-hosted Supabase tomorrow).**

```dart
// lib/features/games/domain/game_repository.dart
abstract interface class GameRepository {
  Future<List<Game>> findGamesNear({
    required double lat,
    required double lng,
    required double radiusKm,
    required GameFilters filters,
  });
  Future<void> joinGame(String gameId, {String? lockCode});
  Future<void> leaveGame(String gameId);
  Stream<Game> watchGame(String gameId);
}

// lib/features/games/data/supabase_game_repository.dart
class SupabaseGameRepository implements GameRepository { ... }

// lib/features/games/data/game_repository_provider.dart
@riverpod
GameRepository gameRepository(GameRepositoryRef ref) =>
    SupabaseGameRepository(ref.read(supabaseClientProvider));
```

A widget that calls `supabase.client.from(...)` is a **review-blocker**. CI lint check (custom analyzer rule) added to enforce.

## Alternatives considered

1. **Direct SDK calls everywhere** — fastest now, catastrophic at migration time. Rejected.
2. **GraphQL gateway in front of Supabase** — over-engineered for our scale; ops burden of running a gateway.
3. **Service classes (procedural)** — looks like a repository but lacks the interface contract that makes swapping implementations cheap.

## Consequences

**Positive:** swap Supabase → self-hosted Supabase = change the concrete repository (same SDK) → done. Swap Supabase → PocketBase = write `PocketbaseGameRepository implements GameRepository`, change the provider, ship. Days, not weeks.

**Negative:** extra files per feature; junior-Onur-in-3-weeks will be tempted to skip the abstraction "just this once."

**Neutral:** repositories must return domain models (`freezed`-backed), never raw `Map<String,dynamic>` from the SDK. Mapping layer is part of the repository's job.

## Cursor enforcement

This note compiles to a Cursor rule (`cursor_rule: true`, `cursor_apply: always`, glob `lib/**/*.dart`). Cursor will refuse / warn on direct SDK calls in widget files.

